qas.question: What is the official title of Delhi's head of state?

answers.text: Lieutenant Governor of the Union Territory of Delhi

qas.question: Who is responsible for appointing the Lieutenant Governor of the Union Territory of Delhi?
Which takes precedent when a law passed by Parliament conflicts with a law passed by Delhi's Legislative assembly?

answers.text: the law enacted by the parliament

qas.question: What government body advises the president on appointing a Lieutenant Governor?
Which government position is given most of the executive powers over Delhi?

answers.text: Chief Minister of the Union Territory of Delhi

context: The head of state of Delhi is the <a0_0>Lieutenant Governor of the Union Territory of Delhi<a0_0/>, appointed by the <a1_0>President of India<a1_0/> on the advice of <a3_0>the Central government<a3_0/> and the post is largely ceremonial, as the <a4_0>Chief Minister of the Union Territory of Delhi<a4_0/> is the head of government and is vested with most of the executive powers. According to the Indian constitution, if a law passed by Delhi's legislative assembly is repugnant to any law passed by the Parliament of India, then <a2_0>the law enacted by the parliament<a2_0/> will prevail over the law enacted by the assembly.
